Important decision before Stage 3

Staff accounts should be real Firebase Auth users, but they must not be normal clients and must not access any other event.

The staff account model should be:

users/{staffUid}
role: "event_staff"
accountStatus: "active"

And the event assignment should be:

events/{eventId}/staff/{staffUid}
uid
eventId
clientUid
fullName
mobile
sex
position
customPosition
email
staffStatus: "active" | "disabled"
createdAt
updatedAt

The staff should only access /staff, and every backend function must check:

Is this authenticated user assigned to this exact event?
Is staffStatus active?
Is the event still valid?

No staff member should be able to read another event, even if it belongs to the same client.

I would adjust your Stage 3 split slightly

Your direction is correct, but I would stage it like this:

3A — Event staff accounts UI tab only

Inside the Event Details page, add a new tab: Staff.

The client can create staff accounts with:

Name
Mobile number
Sex
Position
Email
Password

Positions:

General Supervisor
Security Guard
Entry Organizer
Other

For “Other”, show a custom position field.

This stage is UI only. No backend yet.

3B — Staff /staff page login scaffold only

Build:

/staff/index.html

It has:

Login screen
Basic staff shell
Event details card
Arrived guests list placeholder
Scanner area placeholder
Manual/auto confirmation toggle placeholder

No backend yet.

3C — Staff scanner UI components only

Still frontend only.

Add:

Camera scanner UI placeholder
Manual QR payload input for testing
Scan result panel
Auto confirm toggle
Confirm arrival button
Mark guest leaving / will return button
Rejected reason panel

We can use manual QR input first, then add camera QR scanner after the backend is stable. Camera scanning can be messy on mobile browsers, so manual QR payload testing is the safer first pass.

3D — Backend functions: staff account management

This is where staff accounts are actually created.

Functions:

createEventStaffAccount
listEventStaff
updateEventStaffAccount
disableEventStaffAccount

This backend must use Firebase Admin SDK to create staff Auth users. Do not create staff accounts from the frontend with normal Firebase Auth signup, because that can interfere with the currently logged-in client session.

3E — Backend functions: staff event access + QR verification

Functions:

getMyStaffEventWorkspace
verifyEventGuestQr
confirmGuestArrival
markGuestWillReturn

Core rules:

QR must belong to the same event.
Guest must be accepted.
Guest must not be revoked.
QR pass must be active.
If guest is already arrived, reject unless status is will_return.
If valid, mark arrived.
Store arrival time and staff UID.

Guest status flow should become:

accepted
arrived
will_return
arrived_again
revoked
declined

But we can keep the existing invitationStatus simple and add dedicated fields:

attendanceStatus: "not_arrived" | "arrived" | "will_return"
arrivalCount
lastArrivedAt
lastExitMarkedAt
lastScannedBy

This is cleaner than overloading invitationStatus.

3F — Wire staff account UI to backend

Wire Event Details Staff tab to:

createEventStaffAccount
listEventStaff
disableEventStaffAccount
3G — Wire /staff page to backend

Wire staff login and scanner page to:

getMyStaffEventWorkspace
verifyEventGuestQr
confirmGuestArrival
markGuestWillReturn
About “QR invalid after arrival”

Yes. After a successful arrival scan:

attendanceStatus = "arrived"

If the same QR is scanned again, backend should reject with:

Already arrived

If staff marks guest as “will return”:

attendanceStatus = "will_return"

Then when QR is scanned again, backend allows entry and changes back to:

attendanceStatus = "arrived"
arrivalCount += 1

That gives you a clean re-entry model.

Rejection reasons

The staff page should show clear rejection reasons:

QR does not belong to this event
Invitation was revoked
Guest declined
Guest has not accepted invitation
Guest already arrived
QR pass inactive
Invitation link disabled
Invalid QR format
Staff account not assigned to this event
My recommendation

Yes, proceed to Stage 3, but do not jump straight into backend. Start with:

3A: Event staff accounts UI tab only

Then:

3B: Staff /staff login scaffold only
3C: Staff scanner UI components only
3D: Backend staff account management
3E: Backend QR verification and attendance logic
3F: Wire client staff tab
3G: Wire staff scanner page

